textAnnotations.description:
LAC FILE NUMBER
A221
PHYSICAL STATE
A crystalline solid at room temperature which melts at >56°C.
PM:
SPECIFIC GRAVITY
The pH of a 50% concentration of A221 in water was theoretically
calculated to be 7.26 at 22°C from a 0.5% solution in 79.5% aqueous
dioxane according to the extrapolation procedures of Dr. P. D.
Schickedantz, Lozillard Accession Number 1662. Reference45-10-1.
Not Determined.
SOLUBILITY
MUTAGENICITY SOLVENTS
A221 is soluble in EtOH at 0.2 g/mL, with stirring, at room
temperature. Reference BC30-88.
ORAL
A221 forms a solution in corn oil at 0.5 g/0.5 mL, with stirring
at room temperature. Reference BC30-88.
ACUTE CARDIOVASCULAR
COMPOUND PHYSICAL PARAMETERS
A221 forms a solution in corn oil at 0.5 g/0.5 mL, with stirring
at room temperature. Reference BC30-88.
STORAGE RECOMMENDATIONS
A221 is insoluble for this procedure. Reference BC30-88.
COMPOUND SENSITIVE TO
Refrigerate in an amber glass bottle at no more than 8°C.
